      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Last year's Eureka winner BAY OF BISCAY (6) should be close to his peak following two solid efforts off a spell. Has come from this barrier both times, placing fresh before finishing 3.6m away after racing parked in the City of Melton Plate. Owns a good third-up record so he could find his way back into the winners' list. MY ULTIMATE BARNEY (1) continued his good form when he drew deep and raced three wide before sticking on to place here last start. Led from wider to win at Geelong prior so he can take full advantage of the ace draw. OLIVER DAN (2) has been consistent without winning of late, putting together a string of top-four finishes. Has had five weeks off but gets his best draw for some time. Looks a gap to the others with TRIPLE EIGHT NZ (4) next best.",
